init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The answer to that question lies in the fact that the United States was the only nation to have a nuclear bomb.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The other nations were afraid that if they went into isolation, the United States would use the bomb on them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States, on the other hand, was afraid that if they didnt go into isolation, the other nations would use the bomb on them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States, in order to prevent the other nations from using the bomb on them, decided to use the bomb on them first.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States, on the other hand, had no such issues.
